			<h1>BAYADA Hospice, Burlington Region - Essex Junction, VT</h1>

			<p>Providing <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#Hospice">hospice</a> services for people throughout Vermont, we are located in Post Office Square in the village of Essex Junction on the shores of Lake Champlain. We provide clinical, social, spiritual, and emotional care so our patients can remain at home with comfort, grace, and dignity. Please visit our <a href="services-hospice.asp">services</a> page to learn more about how we can help.</p>
			<p>All care is provided with compassion, excellence, and reliabilityâ€”our core values. We also have teams conveniently located throughout the state, so no matter where you or your loved ones may reside, we will be able to provide the services you need.</p>

			<h2>Experienced hospice team</h2>
			<p>Our experienced professionals are caring members of your community who are focused entirely on hospice care.  Director TylaAnn Burger, RN, CHPCA and her team are passionate about helping people at end-of-life.</p>

			<p>TylaAnn is the only certified hospice administrator in Vermont.  Hospice administrator certification ensures that a person has mastered specific competences related to hospice administration, and demonstrates excellence in the hospice field. </p>

			<h2>Our dedicated office team also includes:</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Community Liaison and Volunteer Coordinator</li>
					<li>Clinical Manager</li>
					<li>Client Services Manager</li>
					<li>Bereavement Program Coordinator</li>
				</ul><br>

			<h2>Volunteers</h2>
			<p>In addition to our office and field teams, volunteers make an important difference in the lives of our patients and their families. Some provide companionship, run errands, or help with other tasks. But no matter what they do, they are a gift! If you or someone you know would like to volunteer with us, please let us know. We provide a flexible training and orientation schedule to meet your needs.</p>

